      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix to combine – this is your <strong>Peruvian-style chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1715615744965-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1715615744965-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1715615744965-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1715615744965-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1715615744965-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon)</p><p>Add the <strong>Peruvian-style chicken</strong> to one side of a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray and add the<strong> halved pepper </strong>to the other side</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for an initial 12 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1715615751964-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1715615751964-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1715615751964-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
